                <h2 data-uuid="dd5705051e554d998d1150fa6ca6bba8"> Document-Based Investigation</h2>
            </div>
            <h3 data-uuid="08c6ac8fa9db4e408dddae3fc4f86eb1">Part 2: Write a Speech</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="bf499c6c40a04ed69f6ba3fa8cf1321b">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="59c3e76a97404ba3a577fefac828bf88">The
                Constitution established a federal system of government for the United States.
                Under this system, responsibilities are divided between the federal and state
                governments. In addition, the Constitution created three separate branches of
                the federal government to help prevent the abuse of power. The framers of the
                Constitution also designed it to be flexible enough to adapt to changes in
                society. This flexibility is achieved through the adoption of amendments. The
                first ten amendments, known as the Bill of Rights, protect the basic rights of
                individuals. </p>
            <h6 data-uuid="f06a8c39a23747e1af77eae870d2764d">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="59bae1782805450dbeaf0c0c0a712364">How
                does the Constitution promote the welfare of ordinary Americans? Write a speech
                in which you explain how the Constitution protects individuals and the nation
                as a whole.</p>
            <p data-uuid="bd6e7b32cae844248bccee88c3019b1c">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your
                speech.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="277e4fc9bb264c4a8ffa0e7434aae52b">
                <li data-uuid="11a6bb98339f4e1cbea81cae2959e170">
                    Review your notes and sources before you start writing.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="f015bbce301340d48104c05d61c48bfb">Use at least <i>three</i>&#160;of the sources in Part 1, and develop the speech with relevant, well-chosen text evidence from the documents.&#160;</li>
                <li data-uuid="a4df44d1b2f641a08c02a9c411ae5d81">Cite
                    specific text evidence from each of the sources in your response.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="7c471363348043a3a78b157efa4dc947">Plan
                    your speech so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a
                    conclusion.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="8a53447f90af4505a003e09497f33863">Organize
                    your speech in a logical way, with clear transitions from section to section.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="66b28e25deb34ea29ba28ec229918af8">Use relevant visuals and technology to support the topic of your speech.</li>
                <li data-uuid="c462e2a05add42ec8a4a68ad4f12d49d">Write
                    a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
